Cookbook

  Start simple.

  * Read the {{{./usage.html}usage}} document to decide how to use the plugin depending on your build and deployment strategies

  * Read the {{{./jnlp-mojos-overview.html}JNLP goals overview}}

  * Start your project using the {{{./examples/inbuilt_templates.html}default inbuilt template}}

  * Start with simple signing using the keytool functionality for your {{{./examples/keystore_gen.html}signing needs}}

  * Test your build (e.g. adding the {{{http://svn.mojo.codehaus.org/mojo/trunk/mojo/webstart-maven-plugin/plugin/src/it/it002/}Jetty server to your project}})

  * Create a custom and more complex JNLP template if you need

